Ghana’s Budget Deficit Widened to 1.5% of GDP in First Quarter

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-05-13T14:49:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/ghana-s-budget-deficit-widened-to-1-5-of-gdp-in-first-quarter.html
Ghana ’s budget deficit widened to
819.2 million cedis ($544 million), or 1.5 percent of gross
domestic product, in the first quarter, said Kwesi Amissah- Arthur, governor of the Bank of  Ghana .  The shortfall was 621.4 million cedis, or 1.4 percent of
GDP, the year earlier, he told reporters in the capital, Accra
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 